The paper proposes a new architecture for sequence labeling, which is a task commonly studied in the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The proposed architecture involves deepening the state transition path and incorporating global information, which are techniques commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of word embeddings and BERT, which are popular tools in NLP and machine learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed architecture on two standard NLP tasks, which may also fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
